computeScore(Renderer) - Method in class ej.mwt.Desktop
Computes the score of the given renderer by comparing the Desktop.getStyle() of the desktop with the Renderer.getManagedStyle() of the specified renderer.
The score is bigger when the renderer matches the style and lower when it does not match.
The score is computed using the RenderingContext.computeScore(int, int) algorithm.

computeScore(Renderer) - Method in interface ej.mwt.Renderable

createImage(Display, int[], int, int, int, int, boolean) - Static method in class ej.microui.io.Image
Creates an immutable image from an int array of pixels for the specified display.
Each pixel value is stored in 0xAARRGGBB format, where the high-order byte contains the alpha channel and the remaining bytes contain color components for red, green and blue, respectively.
